This paper deals with the construction and analysis of cyclic codes, which are commonly used in information theory and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algebraic structures and computations, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of finite fields and sequences also suggests cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories.
